{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The primary translator produces a grammatically coherent translation that preserves the meaning of the source text, not just a word-for-word substitution.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Correctness depends on real NMT output quality (grammar/meaning preservation), which a stub cannot validate (LLM-DEP/MOCK-HIDE=yes). It is a single model-evaluation step, not a multi-agent sequence (MULTI-STEP=no), so Workflow is not required.","test_description":"Call the real translation API on a curated multilingual set and assert semantic adequacy/fluency via human-labeled rubric or trusted automatic quality thresholds; fail on literal-but-incorrect substitutions.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.83,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When the translation API returns a 503 error, the service transparently falls back to the dictionary-based translator without returning an error to the caller.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This behavior is deterministic orchestration/error-handling across modules (API adapter -> fallback translator -> response path). Rejection-gate for higher levels: text is about 'returns a 503 ... falls back ... without returning an error' (plumbing), not model output quality, so Agentic is disqualified; real network/OS behavior is not required because an in-process stubbed adapter can deterministically emit 503 and expose the handoff, so System is disqualified.","test_description":"Wire service + fallback translator + local SQLite repo in-process; make the primary adapter return a 503-shaped error; assert caller gets successful fallback translation and no propagated exception.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.08,"Integration":0.77,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The dictionary-based fallback returns the correct pre-stored translation for phrases that exist in the SQLite database.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is module-to-database handoff (querying SQLite and mapping result), not pure function logic (MOCK-MISS=yes for DB wiring). Rejection-gate: behavior text explicitly scopes to 'pre-stored translation ... in the SQLite database', which excludes model-output dependence (Agentic disqualified) and does not require external OS/network/subprocess beyond local DB wiring (System disqualified).","test_description":"Seed a test SQLite DB with known phrase pairs, invoke fallback translator through repository layer, and assert exact stored translation is returned for hits.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The quality tracking comparison correctly computes edit distance between primary and fallback outputs and stores the metric.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Although edit-distance math alone is Unit-testable, this behavior also requires persistence ('stores the metric'), so minimum boundary is calculator + tracking/store modules together. Rejection-gate: text is deterministic ('computes edit distance ... stores metric') and does not require judging model quality/content, so Agentic is disqualified; no real network/subprocess/OS-only failure mode is required, so System is disqualified.","test_description":"Run quality tracker with fixed primary/fallback strings, verify computed character edit distance against known value, and assert the metric record is persisted in the configured local store.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.3,"Integration":0.62,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When both translators are available, the service returns the primary translation and logs the quality comparison in the background.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is orchestration/state-handoff across service, primary translator, fallback translator, and async logging path. Rejection-gate for higher levels: behavior text is routing/side-effect ordering ('returns the primary translation and logs ... in the background'), not whether model output itself is good, so Agentic is disqualified; can be exercised in-process with deterministic stubs and local store without real network/subprocess, so System is disqualified.","test_description":"With both translators stubbed to deterministic outputs and background worker enabled, assert response uses primary output immediately and that a later persisted/logged quality-comparison event appears.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.06,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.01}}]}
